ECKERSON et al. v. TANNEY et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 6, 1917.) No. 264. Appeal from the District Court of the United States, for the Southern District of New York. Blauvelt & Warren, of New York City (George A. Blauvelt, Francis J. MacIntyre, and Maurice J. O’Callaghan, all of New York City, of couhsel), for appellants. Servia & Cox; of Middletown, N. Y. (Abram J. Rose, of New York City, and Abram F. Servin, of Middletown, N. Y., of counsel), for appellees.

Before COXE, WARD, and HOUGH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (235 Fed. 415) affirmed.
